sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Wednesday caught some positive commentary from analysts at Credit Suisse.
The firm maintained its "Outperform" rating on HD while raising its price target to $55.
That new target suggests an 11% upside to the stock's Tuesday closing price of $49.38.
Credit Suisse also boosted its earnings estimates on HD, citing expectations of continually improved margins.
Home Depot shares were mostly flat in premarket trading Wednesday.
Shares of Home Depot ( HD ) have a 2.35% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $49.38.
The stock has technical support in the $45 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $50-$53 price levels.
